sideling.d:
adv. Sidelong; on the side; laterally; also, obliquely;
   askew.
a. Inclining to one side; directed toward one side; sloping;
   inclined; as, sideling ground.

silicification.d:
n. Thae act or process of combining or impregnating
   with silicon or silica; the state of being so combined or impregnated;
   as, the silicification of wood.

sinistrous.d:
a. Being on the left side; inclined to the left;
   sinistral.
a. Wrong; absurd; perverse.

sinistrously.d:
adv. In a sinistrous manner; perversely; wrongly;
   unluckily.
adv. With a tendency to use the left hand.
